Here is the corrected Tundra program:

```tundra
val items = [
   { amount: 2 },
   { amount: 5 },
   { amount: 7 }
];

var total = 0;
for(item in items) {
  total = total + item.amount;
}

print(total);
```
This program will add up all the 'amount' fields from each record in the 'i
'items' list and print out the result, which should be 14. The previous bug
bug was that it resetting `total` to zero within the loop before adding eac
each new item. That line has been removed so that `total` keeps accumulatin
accumulating its total sum of amounts across all items.
